    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Embedding Model Landscape"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An embedding model is a neural network that maps text \u2014 or other content \u2014 to a fixed-length float vector. Models differ in dimensionality, context window, training objective, and cost. Choosing the wrong one is the most common source of poor retrieval quality in production agent systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Decision tree for selecting an embedding model based on use case: code search leads to voyage-code-3, high-volume retrieval to voyage-3-lite, quality-first retrieval to voyage-3, clustering to voyage-3 or text-embedding-3-large",
          "title": "Embedding Model Selection Decision Tree"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Voyage AI Models (Recommended with Claude)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic recommends Voyage AI models for use with Claude agents. They support the asymmetric "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "input_type"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " parameter, have a 32k-token context window, and are trained specifically for retrieval tasks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import voyageai\n\nclient = voyageai.Client()  # reads VOYAGE_API_KEY\n\n# \u2500\u2500 voyage-3: best general retrieval \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nresult = client.embed(\n    [\"What is cosine similarity?\"],\n    model=\"voyage-3\",\n    input_type=\"query\",\n)\nvec = result.embeddings[0]\nprint(len(vec))   # 1024\n\n# \u2500\u2500 voyage-3-lite: reduced cost, lower quality \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nresult_lite = client.embed(\n    [\"What is cosine similarity?\"],\n    model=\"voyage-3-lite\",\n    input_type=\"query\",\n)\nprint(len(result_lite.embeddings[0]))  # 512\n\n# \u2500\u2500 voyage-code-3: optimised for code \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nresult_code = client.embed(\n    [\"def bubble_sort(arr): ...\"],\n    model=\"voyage-code-3\",\n    input_type=\"document\",\n)\nprint(len(result_code.embeddings[0]))  # 1024\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAI Embedding Models"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAI's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "text-embedding-3"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " series supports "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Matryoshka Representation Learning (MRL)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 you can truncate the output vector to any smaller dimension without retraining. This trades recall quality for storage and search speed. Useful when running approximate nearest-neighbour search at scale."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from openai import OpenAI\n\nclient = OpenAI()   # reads OPENAI_API_KEY\n\n# Full 3072-dim vector\nresp = client.embeddings.create(\n    model=\"text-embedding-3-large\",\n    input=\"What is cosine similarity?\",\n)\nfull_vec = resp.data[0].embedding\nprint(len(full_vec))   # 3072\n\n# MRL truncation: 256 dims \u2014 12x smaller, ~5% recall drop\nresp_small = client.embeddings.create(\n    model=\"text-embedding-3-large\",\n    input=\"What is cosine similarity?\",\n    dimensions=256,\n)\nprint(len(resp_small.data[0].embedding))   # 256\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Open-Source Models via Sentence-Transformers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When data cannot leave your infrastructure, use a locally-hosted model. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "sentence-transformers"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " wraps Hugging Face models behind a simple API. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "BAAI/bge-m3"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the current best open-source option for multilingual retrieval."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pip install sentence-transformers\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\nimport numpy as np\n\n_MODEL = SentenceTransformer(\"BAAI/bge-m3\")   # downloads on first run\n\n\ndef embed_local(\n    texts: list[str],\n    batch_size: int = 32,\n) -> list[list[float]]:\n    vecs = _MODEL.encode(\n        texts,\n        batch_size=batch_size,\n        normalize_embeddings=True,   # unit-normalise for cosine search\n        show_progress_bar=False,\n    )\n    return vecs.tolist()\n\n\nvec = embed_local([\"The cat sat on the mat.\"])[0]\nprint(len(vec))   # 1024 (bge-m3)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
